HUNDREDS of people enjoyed the sunshine yesterday as they took part in the Glasgow Bridges Walk, to raise cash to help find a cure for kidney disease. Purple patch for charity HUNDREDS of people enjoyed the sunshine yesterday as they took part in the Glasgow Bridges Walk, to raise cash to help find a cure for kidney disease.Kidney patients, families and supporters, including Miss Glasgow Merissa Lennon, all donned Kidney Research UK's signature purple for the seven-mile walk across the city's most famous bridges.The charity is hoping to raise around &pound;40,000 for research into kidney disease 